election_record.label: New York 1809 State Senate, Western District

overview.note: "Senatorial Districts -- The federalists have succeeded in the Eastern and Western districts. The gentlemen elected are Messrs Paris and Stearns for the former, and Messrs Platt, Hall and Phelps for the latter. In the Western district, last year the republicans had a majority exceeding 300 votes; this year the federal majority will be between 5 and 700." American Citizen (New York, NY). May 12, 1809. Republican Watch-Tower (New York, NY). May 16, 1809.
Hugh MacNair, Hugh Jameson, Richard Leech, Stephen Phelps and Samuel Lawrence were candidates for Assembly in Ontario County.
